commitResults.messageTitle: added skeleton greeting (level 0)
mimics user and exits when user inputs bye
adds inputs to list
correction to task level 2 to be able to take in a phrase instead of only words
added task class, can mark and unmark tasks
added subclasses of task and edited duke to exhibit polymorphism
handle exceptions
added delete function
using automated testing
extracted out code into respective methods to make it neater. also added some more catch statements to catch more exceptions.
made some methods in Duke.java private
Add HardDisk.java to save the data from running Duke and reload previous data
commitResults.messageBody:
Duke has an additional functionality of allowing data to be saved and reloaded.

HardDisk has a loadList and save function that allows data to be reloaded
and saved respectively.

Functions is seperated from the rest of the code within the harddisk class
as they have a common link in which they both utilise stored data

commitResults.messageTitle: Add DateFormatter.java to convert dates in the format yyyy-mm-dd into a more readable form
commitResults.messageBody:
This will make the dates more readable for the user.

The DateFormatter class is used in the constructors of EventTask and DeadlineTask to
convert the dates.

This is so a more readable date is displayed to the user.

commitResults.messageTitle: Restructure files to have more OOP
commitResults.messageBody:
Everything exists in one file which is messy. Need to seperate file into Ui, Storage, Parser,
TaskList so it is neater.

Seperate code into these different classes. Also seperate commands into classes
that inherit from 1 abstract command class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Restructure files to place in suitable packages
commitResults.messageBody:
Without packages, files are messy and classes are hard to find.

Separated into packages command, run, tasks, and others.

With packages workflow is neater.
